Rollup is a module bundler for JavaScript which compiles small
pieces of code into something larger and more complex, such as a
library or application. It uses the standardized ES module format
for code, instead of previous idiosyncratic solutions such as
CommonJS and AMD. ES modules let you freely and seamlessly combine
the most useful individual functions from your favorite libraries.
Rollup can optimize ES modules for faster native loading in modern
browsers, or output a legacy module format allowing ES module
workflows today.
